Installation
============

```shell
$ bower install --save interact

$ npm install --save interact.js
```

```html
<head>
    <script type="text/javascript" src="/path/to/interact.js"></script>
</head>
```

interact.js can be installed for a project using [Bower](http://bower.io/) or
[npm](https://www.npmjs.org/) or by downloading the script from
http://interactjs.io/#download and linking to the script in a `<script>` tag's
`src` attribute.


`interact` is exposed as an npm module, AMD module, or a global object
depending on what the environment supports.

